This may be one of the top 5 most amazing pieces of woodwork I've ever seen. A giant (47.5 foot) lion carved out of a SINGLE redwood tree. Are you freaking kidding me?!?! Saw this post in the explore feed shared by @mick.gard but it comes from a sculptor named Dengding Rui Yao out of Myanmar who led 20 carvers that made this sculpture over the course of 3 years. The sheer enormity and detail at that size is breath taking. Just had to share with you guys!
#mindblown #sculptingexcellence #fixthisbuildthat
